    QuoteSearchServlet
    The url for delete will return methodNotAllowed The url for post will return methodNotAllowed The url for get will be one of: /quoteSearch/List (retrieves everything) /quoteSearch/<quoteId> (retrieves a single record) /quoteSearch?term= (retrieves everything) /quoteSearch?term=<queryTerm> (retrieves filtered selection) /quoteSearch?sort=<sort>,<sort> (retrieve sorted selection) /quoteSearch?term=<term>&sort=<sort> (retrieve sorted filtered selection)
    QuoteServlet
    The url for delete will be of the form /quote/<quoteId>/<quoteNumber>/<revision> The url for get will be one of: /quote (retrieves everything) /quote/<quoteId> (filters quote table quoteId and quoteNumber /quote/<quoteId>/<quoteNumber>/<revision> (retrieves a single record) The url for adding a new record will be a POST to: /quote/add with parameters in the JSON /quote/copy/<quoteId> The url for update will be a POST to: /quote/<quoteId>/<quoteNumber>/<revision> with parameters in the JSON
    QuoteTableServlet
    The url for delete will return methodNotAllowed The url for post will return methodNotAllowed The url for get will be the following: /quoteTable See DataTables Table plug-in for jQuery at datatables.net for details
    ReorderJobListServlet
    The url for this servlet will be of the form /reorderJobList/<quoteId> The new order of Job Id's will be in the posted JSON data
